[34m│[0m ## IDOR (Insecure Direct Object Reference) Attack Playbook                   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > **IMPORTANT:** All payloads in this playbook are EXAMPLES that must be     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m MODIFIED for your specific target. Replace placeholders like `{ID}`,         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m `{PARAMETER}`, `{TARGET_URL}`, `{OBJECT_ID}` with actual values. Adapt       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m techniques based on:                                                         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > - Target's object reference patterns (numeric, UUID, hashed, etc.)         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > - Parameter names and locations                                            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > - Authorization checks and bypass methods                                  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > - Discovered object relationships                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > IDOR occurs when an application provides direct access to objects based on [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m user-supplied input without proper authorization checks.                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Core Concept                                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Example:**                                                                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Original: https://example.com/profile?user_id=123                            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Attack:   https://example.com/profile?user_id=124                            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m If application doesn't verify the logged-in user has permission to view      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m user_id=124, attacker can access other users' data.                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
